article.headline: Yale 74, Dartmouth 62
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Travis Pinick scored 21 points and Ross Morin added 19 to lead Yale to a 74-62 victory over Dartmouth on Friday night. Dartmouth led 4-2 before the Bulldogs went on a 10-0 run to take the lead for good. Yale (13-14, 8-5 Ivy League) added another 13-0 run later in the first half for a 25-9 lead, cruising the rest of the way. Dartmouth (9-18, 7-6) was led by Jabari Trotter's 13 points, while Alex Barnett and Dan Biber each scored 12. Both teams entered the contest tied for third in the Ivy League and both had outside chances of earning a share of the league title, but Cornell clinched its second straight title with a win on Friday. Yale had eight steals in the first half and finished with 13 for the game. The Big Green had 24 turnovers in the contest.
